                  </persName>
            , JUN. I live in Old Swan-lane, and am <rs id="t18230910-294-viclabel1580" type="occupation">clerk</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-294-victim2564 t18230910-294-viclabel1580"></join> to Messrs. Wigan and Co. On the 11th of August, about nine o'clock in the evening, I was in <placeName id="t18230910-294-crimeloc1581">Crown-street, Finsbury</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-294-crimeloc1581" type="placeName" value="Crown-street, Finsbury"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-294-crimeloc1581" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-294-off1578 t18230910-294-crimeloc1581"></join>, with my handkerchief in my pocket, twisted round my pocket-book. I felt something in my pocket, turned round, and saw my handkerchief pass from the prisoner to his two companions; I seized him immediately - the other two went away towards Bishopsgate-street - I have not found it. I took him to the watch-house.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PLATT. Q. You were walking with two young ladies I believe - A. Yes; one in each arm. I think I saw him about twenty yards below, before he robbed me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-294-person2566">
                  ELIZABETH 
                  EASTWOOD
               <interp inst="t18230910-294-person2566" type="surname" value="EASTWOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-294-person2566" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-294-person2566" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Mr. Newman, and saw the prisoner take his hand out of Mr. Newman's pocket - but could not see what was in it. There were two others with him. Mr. Newman took the prisoner immediately.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. You were looking before you I suppose - A. I turned round immediately as Mr. Newman did - he steped suddenly - I saw him take his hand out of the pocket - but saw no handkerchief in it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was walking the same way as the prosecutor - he turned round suddenly, and said I picked his pocket - I said I had not, and went quietly to the watch-house; if guilty, is it reasonable that I should have gone so quietly.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18230910-294-verdict1582" type="verdictDescription">
